stats - core of almost every detection
table - investigation output
search - Filtering results
where - threshold logic
sort - Prioritization


(EventCode=4624 OR EventCode=4625)
| stats count by Account_Name EventCode
( this is SPL QUERY- Counts successful and failed login events for each account to identify authentication activity patterns.)

(EventCode=4624 OR EventCode=4625)
| stats values(EventCode) as Events by Account_Name
| search Events=4624 Events=4625
(Improved detection - Identifies accounts that experienced both failed and successful logins, which may indicate a successful credential compromise attempt.)

Succesful Logins- Displays successful login events to determine which accounts accessed systems and when. -->  Failed and succesful together - Shows the sequence of successful and failed authentication attempts to identify suspicious login patterns.
--> Most active accounts- Identifies accounts generating the highest number of successful logins, helping analysts prioritize unusual activity. --> Priveleged Logins - Displays accounts that received special administrative privileges, helping identify potentially sensitive or high-risk logins.

MAIN GOAL FOR SOC ANALYST: Determine whether a successful login following failed authentication attempts represents legitimate user activity or potential unauthorized access using valid credentials.
